parameters:
According to multiple sources, in the early Edo
period, there were young female spirit mediums who
traveled from place to place, subduing harmful
mononoke and strange apparitions.

The records concerning her are extensive, with
evidence of her existence even found in the
archives of feudal lords. It's clear that she was
not merely a figure of folklore or fairy tales,
yet her true nature remains enigmatic.

It is said that she was a young and beautiful
shrine maiden with white hair, skilled enough to
calm a mysterious bird that disturbed the capital
with a single stroke of her blade.

It is said that she loved children enough to
exorcise spirits that cursed infants and to care
for sick children, and for some reason, she used a
small shrine as her base of operations and rarely
left it.

It is said that while she saved many people, her
name has not been passed down, and at some point,
she suddenly vanished without a trace.

All of these aspects draw my interest inexorably.
Who was she? I intend to continue my research.
Authored by Eijiro Osako.
